## High-Blast-Radius Files

List the files that, when touched, force **Deep** review regardless of how small the change appears.

- `settings.json` — hook registration map; every wired hook fires from here <!-- auto: 14 inbound doc/script refs + listed in rules/auto-correct-scope.md Rule 4 — high -->
- `hooks/*.sh` (any wired hook) — auto-runs on every matching trigger in every session <!-- auto: Rule 4 high-blast list + 10 contract tests pinned in tests/hooks/ — high -->
- `tests/lib.sh` — shared test harness; all 12 `*.test.sh` files source it <!-- auto: 14 inbound refs across tests/docs — high -->
- `skills/visual-planner/render_plan.py` — core deterministic skill engine (PLAN.md → HTML) <!-- auto: Rule 4 high-blast list + 9 inbound refs + pinned by test_render_plan.py — high -->
- `scripts/run-tests.sh` + `scripts/lint-doc-truth.sh` — CI entry point and doc-truth gate; a change alters what every PR is checked against <!-- auto: CI workflow harness-ci.yml runs these on ubuntu+macos — medium -->
- `templates/SUMMARY.template.md` — defines the `Lane:` line parsed by `hooks/risk-corroboration.sh` <!-- auto: field consumed programmatically by a wired hook — medium -->

> Add new entries when a single file becomes a bottleneck for many features. An empty list means the Deep override loses a key signal.

