## Shared Runtime Contracts

Configuration objects, modules, or protocol shapes whose contract change affects many call sites.

- `settings.json` hook-registration shape — trigger keys (`PreToolUse`, `PostToolUse`, `UserPromptSubmit`, `SessionEnd`) map hooks to events; the CLAUDE.md hook table must stay in sync (doc-truth lint enforces it) <!-- auto: grep of settings.json + lint-doc-truth.sh — high -->
- Hook exit-code/stdout contract — exit 0 = pass, non-zero = block, stderr/stdout = user-visible warning; changing block↔warn semantics affects every commit <!-- auto: inferred from hooks + tests/hooks/*.test.sh assertions — medium -->
- `templates/*.template.md` (SUMMARY, ESCALATIONS, TEST_MATRIX) — artifact shapes consumed by orchestration rules and hooks (`Lane:`, `### Verify`, `### Rollback`) <!-- auto: parsed by risk-corroboration.sh + referenced by rules/orchestration.md — medium -->

