## Entry Point Patterns

For the Quick condition: any change inside these is **NOT** Quick.

- `hooks/` — every wired hook auto-runs on its trigger in every session <!-- auto — high -->
- `settings.json` — registration; a one-line change wires/unwires automation <!-- auto — high -->
- `skills/*/SKILL.md` — user-invocable entry points (`/skill-name`) <!-- auto — high -->
- `scripts/install-harness.sh`, `scripts/deploy-harness.sh` — deployment entry points that mutate target repos <!-- auto: git churn top-20 + install tests — medium -->

---

## Notes for maintainers

- **High-blast list is the highest-leverage signal** — `settings.json` + `hooks/` dominate: they execute automatically in every session of every consuming repo.
- **Doc-truth coupling** — CI fails when docs reference missing paths or the CLAUDE.md hook table contradicts `settings.json`; treat doc/table edits near `hooks/` as coupled changes.
- **`specs/` is local-only** — decisions there don't travel; durable decisions belong in `docs/solutions/` (decision track).
